1
00:00:11,180 --> 00:00:13,080
(Yoon San Ha)

2
00:00:16,820 --> 00:00:18,720
(Arin)

3
00:00:25,230 --> 00:00:27,230
(Yoo Jung Hoo)

4
00:00:30,500 --> 00:00:32,470
(Chuu)

5
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:39,040
(My Girlfriend is the Man!)

6
00:00:50,220 --> 00:00:53,650
You've really aged, my dear grandpa.

7
00:00:56,220 --> 00:00:57,660
My grandma.

8
00:01:17,240 --> 00:01:18,810
So, it is because of your girlfriend.

9
00:01:19,480 --> 00:01:20,550
No.

10
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:22,450
It's because of me.

11
00:01:22,820 --> 00:01:25,649
Yoon Jae. If she truly loves you,

12
00:01:25,650 --> 00:01:27,590
she'll stand by you and encourage you to follow your dreams.

13
00:01:27,860 --> 00:01:30,020
Are you not even getting the treatment you deserve from her?

14
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:31,190
Let's drop this.

15
00:01:48,580 --> 00:01:50,410
There's one thing I know for sure.

16
00:01:51,710 --> 00:01:53,810
At least in this very moment, no one cares about you...

17
00:01:54,180 --> 00:01:56,720
more deeply than me on this planet.

18
00:02:13,370 --> 00:02:14,400
Who are you?

19
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,600
Hey.

20
00:02:15,900 --> 00:02:16,970
Hi.

21
00:02:18,610 --> 00:02:20,240
Sorry I'm late.

22
00:02:29,420 --> 00:02:31,390
Well, this is...

23
00:02:32,190 --> 00:02:34,150
Let me explain what happened.

24
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:37,760
You don't need to explain.

25
00:02:38,190 --> 00:02:39,190
Come on.

26
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:45,200
Yoon Jae's girlfriend, right?

27
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,339
What are you doing here?

28
00:02:48,340 --> 00:02:49,400
We can talk later.

29
00:02:54,070 --> 00:02:55,080
Come on.

30
00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:01,280
That's right. I'm Yoon Jae's girlfriend.

31
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:06,950
I'm pretty close with Ji Hoon's grandpa too.

32
00:03:11,390 --> 00:03:12,960
Hold on. You came here dressed like that?

33
00:03:17,460 --> 00:03:20,000
Yes, why?

34
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,240
Where is Ji Hoon?

35
00:03:26,070 --> 00:03:27,470
Ji Hoon?

36
00:03:29,980 --> 00:03:34,050
Well, Ji Hoon is...

37
00:03:34,620 --> 00:03:36,420
Oh, Ji Hoon!

38
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,620
He went back to Seoul.

39
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:41,820
He went back to Seoul?

40
00:03:42,390 --> 00:03:43,460
When?

41
00:03:43,590 --> 00:03:44,660
Earlier.

42
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:49,899
He said something urgent came up and left.

43
00:03:49,900 --> 00:03:50,900
Right.

44
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,070
My gosh.

45
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:03,080
Aren't those Ji Hoon's shoes?

46
00:04:06,950 --> 00:04:08,550
Darn it, they are.

47
00:04:14,990 --> 00:04:17,189
Maybe he got mixed up and put on the wrong shoes...

48
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:18,530
since it was so dark?

49
00:04:18,830 --> 00:04:20,560
- What? - Oh, yes.

50
00:04:21,530 --> 00:04:23,160
That must be it.

51
00:04:24,100 --> 00:04:26,400
Am I the only one who thinks this is weird?

52
00:04:26,930 --> 00:04:29,200
This girl shows up out of nowhere,

53
00:04:29,500 --> 00:04:31,769
and Ji Hoon suddenly disappears without a word? What's going on?

54
00:04:31,770 --> 00:04:35,040
All sorts of wild and unexpected things can happen in life.

55
00:04:52,830 --> 00:04:54,330
The important thing now is that...

56
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:57,830
Kim Ji Eun, Park Yoon Jae's girlfriend,

57
00:04:59,170 --> 00:05:01,030
has returned.

58
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:12,710
I missed you,

59
00:05:14,550 --> 00:05:15,550
Yoon Jae.

60
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,560
Sorry for making you wait so long.

61
00:05:37,970 --> 00:05:41,580
(Episode 10: 6734)

62
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:45,910
Here.

63
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:49,150
I made this all-natural syrup completely from scratch.

64
00:05:49,380 --> 00:05:52,289
It's nice to add it to hot water and drink as tea on cold days.

65
00:05:52,290 --> 00:05:54,959
Grandpa, how come you're giving me so many things?

66
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,789
Perilla leaf kimchi, mustard leaf kimchi,

67
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:58,030
and sweet potato vine kimchi.

68
00:05:58,690 --> 00:06:01,500
I only packed the things you absolutely love.

69
00:06:02,360 --> 00:06:05,230
By the way, are you really Yoon Jae's girlfriend?

70
00:06:07,130 --> 00:06:09,700
Oh, yes.

71
00:06:10,870 --> 00:06:12,110
I told you about him.

72
00:06:12,510 --> 00:06:14,370
This is Min Hyuk, my co-worker at the cafe.

73
00:06:15,180 --> 00:06:16,180
Yes.

74
00:06:16,740 --> 00:06:19,410
I've heard a lot about you. Nice to meet you.

75
00:06:20,610 --> 00:06:23,449
Anyway, Grandpa. What happened to Ji Hoon?

76
00:06:23,450 --> 00:06:25,349
What was so urgent that he left us at your place...

77
00:06:25,350 --> 00:06:26,489
and rushed back to Seoul alone?

78
00:06:26,490 --> 00:06:28,459
Oh, what happened was...

79
00:06:28,460 --> 00:06:30,060
Goodness, what was it?

80
00:06:31,230 --> 00:06:34,600
Oh, dear. He told me, but I forgot the moment I turned around.

81
00:06:35,130 --> 00:06:37,930
This is why it's hard being old sometimes.

82
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:44,940
The phone is turned off. Please leave a message after the tone.

83
00:06:45,270 --> 00:06:47,570
Well, his phone is off.

84
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:49,310
What if something happened to him?

85
00:06:49,580 --> 00:06:51,410
I let it slip my mind briefly,

86
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,549
but he's never straightforward with anything.

87
00:06:53,550 --> 00:06:56,620
No, you're wrong about that.

88
00:06:56,950 --> 00:07:00,050
My grandchild is genuinely honest and kind.

89
00:07:00,290 --> 00:07:01,990
Did he call or text you at all?

90
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:03,420
No, he didn't.

91
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:06,930
Stop asking so many questions.

92
00:07:07,330 --> 00:07:08,730
I'm sure he had his reasons.

93
00:07:09,230 --> 00:07:10,260
Let's go.

94
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:11,570
Well...

95
00:07:11,870 --> 00:07:13,199
You guys can go ahead.

96
00:07:13,200 --> 00:07:15,470
I need to stay and take care of something.

97
00:07:15,940 --> 00:07:17,140
Me too.

98
00:07:17,840 --> 00:07:18,940
What do you need to do?

99
00:07:19,240 --> 00:07:20,670
As if that's any of your business.

100
00:07:21,040 --> 00:07:22,180
Come on. Let's go.

101
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:24,179
What's your problem?

102
00:07:24,180 --> 00:07:26,479
- What's with you, Yu Ri? - Get going. I'll call you.

103
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,949
- Get going, guys. - I'll call you.

104
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:29,250
- Let go! - Bye.

105
00:07:29,350 --> 00:07:30,850
What's your deal?

106
00:07:32,390 --> 00:07:33,520
My gosh.

107
00:07:36,490 --> 00:07:38,660
Hey, seriously.

108
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:41,260
Don't worry.

109
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:43,929
It's beyond what ordinary people...

110
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:46,070
could ever imagine, even in their wildest dreams.

111
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,540
Oh, boy.

112
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,880
You must have been really shocked.

113
00:07:59,050 --> 00:08:00,810
You must've been shocked.

114
00:08:02,580 --> 00:08:06,349
This isn't my first rodeo, so it was all right.

115
00:08:06,350 --> 00:08:08,090
What? "First rodeo?"

116
00:08:09,820 --> 00:08:12,290
You're adorable.

117
00:08:13,260 --> 00:08:14,999
Oh, I need to go to the bathroom.

118
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,000
Sure.

119
00:08:26,410 --> 00:08:27,470
My gosh.

120
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:30,440
You're so beautiful.

121
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,310
When I see you,

122
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:37,080
I'm reminded of your mother when she was young.

123
00:08:38,990 --> 00:08:40,920
- Grandma. - You know, Ji Eun,

124
00:08:41,290 --> 00:08:44,220
you were so cool yesterday too.

125
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:49,860
Yu Ri said the same thing.

126
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:54,030
Except for the fact that I changed into a man, it's still a win.

127
00:08:54,470 --> 00:08:57,070
Of course. That's still you too, you know?

128
00:08:57,900 --> 00:08:58,970
Ji Eun.

129
00:08:59,270 --> 00:09:02,510
If you ever change back into a man, try not to resent yourself too much.

130
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:05,449
You can't expect others to acknowledge you...

131
00:09:05,450 --> 00:09:08,750
if you don't love yourself.

132
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:12,150
This is true for everyone, ordinary people included.

133
00:09:16,190 --> 00:09:17,659
Okay, I'll try.

134
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:18,660
Good.

135
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:22,800
Oh, my.

136
00:09:39,350 --> 00:09:40,350
Ji Hoon!

137
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,380
Hey, Ji Hoon.

138
00:09:46,950 --> 00:09:47,950
My gosh.

139
00:09:55,300 --> 00:09:57,229
What did Grandpa pack for you in here?

140
00:09:57,230 --> 00:09:58,929
Hey, are you sure this is kimchi?

141
00:09:58,930 --> 00:10:00,430
- Put them here. - Oh, boy.

142
00:10:02,970 --> 00:10:04,040
Thanks.

143
00:10:04,700 --> 00:10:07,340
Grandpa's kimchi is to die for.

144
00:10:07,710 --> 00:10:09,140
Do you want to stay for some ramyeon?

145
00:10:13,210 --> 00:10:14,210
Well...

146
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:16,380
Shall I?

147
00:10:20,690 --> 00:10:21,959
Hey, your place is really nice.

148
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,290
Oh, wait.

149
00:10:24,320 --> 00:10:27,129
Can you give me a moment to get ready?

150
00:10:27,130 --> 00:10:28,130
What?

151
00:10:28,131 --> 00:10:30,560
Don't turn around. Stay right here, okay?

152
00:10:32,170 --> 00:10:34,470
Hey, get ready for what? I thought we were just having ramyeon.

153
00:10:35,500 --> 00:10:36,500
Goodness.

154
00:10:37,870 --> 00:10:39,310
Gosh, this is nuts.

155
00:10:39,810 --> 00:10:40,870
Get ready for what?

156
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:47,050
Actually, forget it.

157
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:48,779
Today, you should just go.

158
00:10:48,780 --> 00:10:50,549
I'll invite you over next time.

159
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:53,220
What's there to get ready for if we're eating ramyeon?

160
00:10:53,450 --> 00:10:55,319
Oh, you don't have any ramyeon? I can pick some up.

161
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:57,290
No, there's plenty here.

162
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:58,560
Sorry.

163
00:10:58,561 --> 00:11:00,789
- I'll invite you when I'm ready. - What?

164
00:11:00,790 --> 00:11:02,160
Hey, wait... What?

165
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:37,999
I'll just go alone from here.

166
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:39,929
Why? I don't like that.

167
00:11:39,930 --> 00:11:41,000
Let me walk you home.

168
00:11:41,170 --> 00:11:43,470
Have you forgotten who my neighbour is?

169
00:11:45,170 --> 00:11:46,310
Darn it.

170
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:50,140
But why does that matter?

171
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:53,480
What do you mean? What will you say, then?

172
00:11:55,020 --> 00:11:57,280
Well, I'll just say...

173
00:11:58,450 --> 00:11:59,750
you two are cousins?

174
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,320
How about that?

175
00:12:01,490 --> 00:12:04,790
He was only staying temporarily because of his circumstances.

176
00:12:05,030 --> 00:12:08,829
Ji Hoon has returned home.

177
00:12:08,830 --> 00:12:10,600
The farther the better, right?

178
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,070
How about the US?

179
00:12:13,330 --> 00:12:16,740
Come on. That's too random.

180
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:19,070
We need to set things up properly from the start.

181
00:12:20,410 --> 00:12:21,940
When it comes to Kang Min Joo,

182
00:12:22,540 --> 00:12:25,180
I don't want to just wing it or handle things sloppily.

183
00:13:03,180 --> 00:13:05,550
Hey, didn't you get my text?

184
00:13:07,050 --> 00:13:09,190
We meet again.

185
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:12,230
What are you doing here?

186
00:13:12,560 --> 00:13:14,060
Shouldn't I be asking you that?

187
00:13:17,000 --> 00:13:20,169
All right. Come and sit here.

188
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:21,940
Hey, sister. Leave us alone.

189
00:13:23,140 --> 00:13:24,200
"Sister?"

190
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:28,110
Are you sure?

191
00:13:28,310 --> 00:13:29,310
Yes.

192
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:45,760
In situations where we shouldn't be meeting...

193
00:13:46,730 --> 00:13:49,800
I mean, why do we keep crossing paths in places we shouldn't?

194
00:13:51,300 --> 00:13:54,130
Why are you here?

195
00:13:55,670 --> 00:13:58,470
I live here now.

196
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,740
Ji Hoon is...

197
00:14:02,140 --> 00:14:03,410
He's my cousin.

198
00:14:03,780 --> 00:14:06,910
He was staying here temporarily because of his circumstances.

199
00:14:07,310 --> 00:14:08,650
You two are cousins?

200
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:12,990
And you expect me to believe that now?

201
00:14:13,890 --> 00:14:16,460
It's up to you whether you believe me or not.

202
00:14:19,060 --> 00:14:21,030
So, where is Ji Hoon now?

203
00:14:22,130 --> 00:14:23,200
Well...

204
00:14:24,060 --> 00:14:26,030
I guess he went back home.

205
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:28,070
Oh, right.

206
00:14:28,300 --> 00:14:30,440
Just so you know, his home is in the US.

207
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:33,540
Just by looking, you can tell he grew up in the US.

208
00:14:44,050 --> 00:14:47,590
Does Yoon Jae know about this situation too?

209
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:49,290
Yes.

210
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:52,960
He walked me home just now.

211
00:14:57,760 --> 00:14:59,230
Can you please leave now?

212
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:01,170
I'm quite tired.

213
00:15:11,710 --> 00:15:12,950
Hey, the door isn't that way!

214
00:15:17,820 --> 00:15:19,320
I see that he left all his stuff.

215
00:15:21,860 --> 00:15:22,890
Well...

216
00:15:23,290 --> 00:15:26,430
He probably left those because he didn't need them.

217
00:15:27,890 --> 00:15:30,600
I'm sure he took all the important things with him.

218
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,380
You did well, Kim Ji Eun.

219
00:16:09,270 --> 00:16:10,770
I have to organise everything again.

220
00:16:15,780 --> 00:16:18,009
(Kang Min Joo)

221
00:16:18,010 --> 00:16:20,279
I understand you had to leave, but you could've at least said goodbye.

222
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,449
I'm sad.

223
00:16:21,450 --> 00:16:22,850
I want to make sure you're okay.

224
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:24,550
Text me back when you get this.

225
00:16:25,550 --> 00:16:26,550
What?

226
00:16:27,750 --> 00:16:28,960
So she wasn't suspicious?

227
00:16:29,590 --> 00:16:30,920
She was just worried?

228
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:37,230
Kim Ji Eun, snap out of it.

229
00:16:40,930 --> 00:16:41,970
Seriously...

230
00:17:06,060 --> 00:17:07,460
Goodness. Can't you knock?

231
00:17:10,900 --> 00:17:12,900
- Here, this is for you. - What is this?

232
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:14,970
Socks.

233
00:17:15,870 --> 00:17:17,439
I got matching socks for you and Mr. Kim.

234
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,070
You guys can't really wear other matching couples' stuff.

235
00:17:19,570 --> 00:17:21,810
Hey, aren't I the best sister in the world?

236
00:17:23,510 --> 00:17:26,079
Oh, right. Ji Hoon is done tutoring you.

237
00:17:26,080 --> 00:17:28,450
- I mean, he can't do it anymore. - What? Why not?

238
00:17:28,650 --> 00:17:29,880
Ask no more.

239
00:17:30,850 --> 00:17:33,319
I'll let Mom know, so don't say anything.

240
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:35,519
Something's fishy about this. Did you guys fight?

241
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,019
There's nothing fishy about it.

242
00:17:37,020 --> 00:17:38,859
Hey, get out. Go.

243
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:40,389
- What's this? Let me see. - What? Nothing.

244
00:17:40,390 --> 00:17:42,500
- Get out! Go. - My goodness.

245
00:17:42,660 --> 00:17:44,630
- Unbelievable. - Hey, also...

246
00:17:45,770 --> 00:17:47,200
- Always knock before you come in. - No, I won't.

247
00:17:55,540 --> 00:17:58,980
(Exchange Student Application for Semester 1, 2025)

248
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:14,760
My gosh.

249
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:23,270
Let me show you.

250
00:18:23,600 --> 00:18:25,610
Don't talk. Just stay still, okay?

251
00:18:25,810 --> 00:18:27,009
Okay, got it.

252
00:18:27,010 --> 00:18:28,370
I told you not to talk.

253
00:18:32,210 --> 00:18:35,780
Use diagonal strokes moving downward and move slowly.

254
00:19:00,340 --> 00:19:03,140
So, you had some good memories too, after all.

255
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,189
(Delivery Instructions, Special Requests)

256
00:19:17,190 --> 00:19:18,759
(Could you throw in a few extra fish balls, please?)

257
00:19:18,760 --> 00:19:20,059
(I love fish balls!)

258
00:19:20,060 --> 00:19:22,130
Yoon Jae. Could you go and get more fish balls?

259
00:19:22,400 --> 00:19:24,100
Fish balls here are tasty.

260
00:19:25,200 --> 00:19:26,200
Fish balls?

261
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:37,010
- What? - Your food's right at your door.

262
00:19:37,340 --> 00:19:38,880
Is Ji Hoon here, by any chance?

263
00:19:39,010 --> 00:19:40,480
I told you he wasn't coming back.

264
00:19:46,390 --> 00:19:47,550
Fine, I'm not curious either.

265
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:03,240
How annoying.

266
00:20:09,910 --> 00:20:11,640
- Mom. - Hey, there you are.

267
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:14,280
What a nice day.

268
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:16,850
Nice, my foot. Aren't you cold?

269
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:18,820
- No, I'm fine. - Here, wear this.

270
00:20:20,290 --> 00:20:21,290
Have you eaten yet?

271
00:20:21,420 --> 00:20:23,220
Of course, I have. I was with your aunt, you know.

272
00:20:24,490 --> 00:20:25,530
What about you?

273
00:20:25,730 --> 00:20:27,689
I hope you're eating well while studying.

274
00:20:27,690 --> 00:20:28,700
